text:
Terrible food.
Tomato chutney was spoiled.
Idli was tough and microwaved.
Paneer kadai was so salty I had to dilute with water and even then had to throw it away because still too salty.

Ordered via grab but kitchen took one entire hour to prepare even though I asked for fast delivery.

Extremely incompetent, got my order wrong and sent me matar masala instead of matar pulao.

I ordered six different biryanis and some starters for a dinner party. The food was delivered on time, and we received extra starters as part of the combo. We enjoyed all six biryanis, each with a unique taste. I highly recommend the Mysore mutton biryani; the mutton biryani is a must-try. The spice levels were just right, and the portions were generous. Overall, it was an absolute biryani party. Thanks to the restaurant for the great food!

The foods are delicious, specially The Chicken Dum Biryani!!
